<br>
I just finished poking around in Muspelheim and picked me up the Fireforged sword, which, at my level (24) has an effective DPS of 8.4 (I think, could be slightly different than that). Anyway, the Njessi Carved Fang 2-handed sword that I just received from the Silent Death quest has EXACTLY the same effective DPS.<br>
<br>
The Fireforged sword has a speed of 2.4, and I'm literally able to hit my style key while I'm in the air (spinning from Assault) and as soon as my feet land I style again.<br>
<br>
Both swords add to my sword skill, though I think the Fireforged sword adds +4 and Njessi's adds +3.<br>
<br>
I've heard from people that there is a 15% damage bonus on using 2-handed weapons. Is that information reflected in Delve or is it added to your swings? So, if the effective DPS of a 2-hander is 8 (to make the math easier), and it swings every 4.2 seconds, if there is a 15% bonus  ... how does that work out in real numbers?<br>
<br>
Essentially my plan is this:<br>
<br>
If I'm in a group where I'm the lowest guy and not the main tank, I'll be picking out my 2-hander. If I'm soloing I'll be using the 1h/shield because I (kobold) block like a madman. Should I be doing it differently considering both weapons have the same DPS? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/5/02 6:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> DPS</span><hr size=1> The 15% bonus is NOT counted in the base/clamped/effective DPS calcuations. You'll hit 15% harder with a 2H weapon than with the 1H weapon if they both have the same listed DPS.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uarkadi2002.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkadi2002</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/02 12:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DPS</span><hr size=1> So, in other words, when comparing two weapons and deciding which one to use, the ONLY time I should consider swapping to sword-and-board mode is when my 1hander has AT LEAST 15% more effective DPS than the two-hander?<br>
<br>
Cripes I've been using the lower-damage weapon the whole time then. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ueregil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eregil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/Eregil.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/10/02 4:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.iol.it/okandrea/ereliz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DPS</span><hr size=1> There are only 2 times I would consider using a 1h weapon:<br>
<br>
- Fighting a bubble caster like a warden as 2h hammers are to slow.<br>
<br>
